Shrinkage Methods

# Ridge Regression and Lasso Regression
train <- read.csv("/Users/kevinveeder/Desktop/R/MSU/STT481_Capstone/Project_stt481/train_new.csv")
test <- read.csv("/Users/kevinveeder/Desktop/R/MSU/STT481_Capstone/Project_stt481/test_new.csv")

#normalizing data
mean <- apply(train, 2, mean)
std <- apply(train, 2, sd)
train_data <- scale(train, center = mean, scale = std)
test_data <- scale(test, center = mean, scale = std)

# pt1---- splitting data 

set.seed(123)
partition <- createDataPartition(y = train$SalePrice, p = 0.7, list = F)
training_data <- train[partition, ]
testing_data <- train[-partition, ]

set.seed(123)
partition_training <- createDataPartition(y = training_data$SalePrice, p = 0.8, list = F)
training <- training_data[partition_training, ]
validation <- training_data[-partition_training, ]

# pt3 --- lasso
# now to evaluate variables with high predictor values
x <- model.matrix(~.,training_data[,-24])
y <- training_data$SalePrice
cv.out <- cv.glmnet(x,y,alpha=1,type.measure = "mse")
lambda_min <- cv.out$lambda.min
lambda_1se <- cv.out$lambda.1se
coef <- as.matrix(coef(cv.out,s=lambda_1se))
coef2 <- as.data.frame(as.table(coef))
coef2 <- coef2[,-2]%>%filter(Freq != 0)%>%rename(Variable = Var1, Coeficients = Freq)
coef2

  trControl = trainControl(

# Choosing Among Models using Cross-Validation: --------------------------

predict.regsubsets <- function (object, newdata , id, ...){
form <- as.formula(object$call[[2]]) # formula of null model
mat <- model.matrix(form, newdata) # building an "X" matrix from newdata
coefi <- coef(object, id = id) # coefficient estimates associated with the object model containing 
xvars <- names(coefi) # names of the non-zero coefficient estimates
return(mat[,xvars] %*% coefi) # X[,non-zero variables] %*% Coefficients[non-zero variables]
}

# 10-fold cross validation
fold.index <- cut(sample(1:nrow(train)), breaks=10, labels=FALSE)
cv.error.best.fit <- rep(0,19)
for(i in 1:19){ # try different numbers of variables
cat("i=", i,"\n")
error <- rep(0, 10)
for (k in 1:10){
House.train <- train[fold.index != k,]
House.test <- train[fold.index == k,]
true.y <- House.test[,"SalePrice"]
best.fit <- regsubsets(SalePrice ~ ., data = House.train, nvmax = 19)
pred <- predict(best.fit, House.train, id = i)
error[k] <- mean((pred - true.y)^2)
}
print(mean(error))
cv.error.best.fit[i] <- mean(error)
}
